        //Fires click event of search button if enter key is pressed
        function clickButton(e, buttonid) {
            var bt = document.getElementById(buttonid);
            if (typeof bt == 'object') {
                if ((navigator.appName.indexOf("Netscape") > (-1)) || (navigator.appName.indexOf("Opera") > (-1))) {
                    if (e.keyCode == 13) {
                        bt.click();
                        return false;
                    }
                }
                if (navigator.appName.indexOf("Microsoft Internet Explorer") > (-1)) {
                    if (event.keyCode == 13) {
                        bt.click();
                        return false;
                    }
                }
            }
        }

         </div>
         <div class="paragraph">
          <h3>
           <span id="ctl00_cscContentPlaceHolder_newsdetails_NewsDate">
            December 06, 2016
           </span>
          </h3>
         </div>
         <div class="paragraph">
          <h2>
           Sunset Notice – GeneSifter Lab Edition
          </h2>
         </div>
         As per the PerkinElmer Informatics Product Life Cycle, which is located at: www.perkinelmer.com/informatics/support/LifeCycle/, GeneSifter Lab Edition has entered the Sunset phase, effective December 6, 2016. Unless otherwise provided, the Sunset phase shall end one (1) year from the effective date immediately above. On December 5, 2017, GeneSifter Lab Edition will reach End of Life (“EOL”). During the Sunset phase, we will continue to provide support to each Customer with an active Subscription or Support and Maintenance Plan for this Product, as further described below. Except for the support options described in the PerkinElmer Informatics Product Life Cycle, once EOL is reached PerkinElmer will no longer provide support or hosting services for GeneSifter Lab Edition.
         <br/>
         <div class="paragraph">
          <a href="http://www.cambridgesoft.com/support/LifeCycle/">
           Product Life Cycle
          </a>
         </div>
        </td>
